CAUTION:

  • Orange wire harnesses and connectors indicate high-voltage circuits. To prevent electric shock, always follow the procedure described in the repair manual.

    Click here

  • To prevent electric shock, wear insulated gloves when working on wire harnesses and components of the high voltage system.
  • To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE SERVICE PLUG GRIP

Click here

2. REMOVE REAR NO. 1 FLOOR BOARD

Click here

3. REMOVE REAR DECK FLOOR BOX

Click here

4. REMOVE INVERTER TERMINAL COVER

Click here

5. CHECK TERMINAL VOLTAGE

Click here

6. DISCONNECT REAR TRACTION MOTOR CABLE

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Using an insulated tool, remove the 5 bolts and disconnect the rear traction motor cable from the rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Keep the rear traction motor cable terminals and their installation area free from foreign matter, water, etc.
  • Do not touch the waterproof seal or terminals of the rear traction motor cable.
  • Do not damage the terminals, connector housing or rear hybrid motor control inverter assembly during disconnection.
  • Insulate the disconnected terminals with insulating tape.
  • Cover the hole where the rear traction motor cable was installed with tape or equivalent (non-residue type) to prevent entry of foreign matter.

*a

Waterproof Seal

(b) Disengage the clamp.

(c) Separate the grommet of the rear traction motor cable from the vehicle body and push out the rear traction motor cable from the cabin.

7. TEMPORARILY INSTALL INVERTER TERMINAL COVER

Click here

8. REMOVE REAR SUSPENSION MEMBER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

9. REMOVE MAIN MUFFLER HEAT INSULATOR RH

(a) Remove the 4 nuts and main muffler heat insulator RH from the vehicle body.

10. REMOVE REAR TRACTION MOTOR BREATHER PLUG

Click here

11. REMOVE REAR TRACTION MOTOR CABLE

CAUTION:

Be sure to wear insulated gloves.

(a) Disengage the 3 clamps.

(b) Remove the 3 bolts and slide the connector cover as shown in the illustration.

(c) Disengage the 2 claws to remove the motor cable terminal cap from the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.

(d) Using an insulated tool, remove the 3 bolts and rear traction motor cable from the rear traction motor with transaxle assembly.

NOTICE:

  • Keep the rear traction motor cable terminals and their installation area free from foreign matter, water, etc.
  • Do not touch the waterproof seal or terminals of the rear traction motor cable.
  • Cover the hole where the rear traction motor cable was installed with tape or equivalent (non-residue type) to prevent entry of foreign matter.

*a

Waterproof Seal
